===Noun===
'''swift boat'''
# a small, shallow draft water vessel used by the United States Navy for counterinsurgency (COIN) operations during the Vietnam War; Fast Patrol Craft (PCF).

===Transitive Verb===
'''to swift boat'''
# to put forth sensational, difficult-to-disprove allegations about an political figure as part of a public relations campaign against him/her

====Etymology====
From the Swift Boat Veterans for Truth's attacks during the 2004 U.S. presidential campaign.